92762a615-01-04 92762a6Mandala SDS Bishop / Buttermilks Soft92762a6 92762a6It's funny when everything clicks; we put so much time into trying to perfect something, and when it happens it's so fast and fleeting, and an hour later it feels like some kind of fever dream.

Around 20 days over 4 seasons, harder for me than D. North. This climb is very morpho and I think I have the shortest span of anyone (except maybe Megos who thought 8B+) who's done it the big boy way. 34b5a7cd15-06-28 34b5a7cdThe Holy Rails SDS Tuolumne Meadows / Marijuolumne Dome Talus Hard34b5a7cd 34b5a7cdAKA The Holy Mountain...12 days, 3 seasons, and many tears literal and metaphorical shed. What a journey...from doing the stand in a day, to working out the sit on day two, then falling on the crux move from the sit probably 50 times over the last two years. Really wish I could have been there to battle for the FA last fall but "the glory is not for you, Didier"

If we base how difficult we think something is on the likelyhood of being able to repeat a problem in a day given perfect conditions, this might be my hardest send. Happy to confirm the cuspy but inconclusive slash grade. Youngblood Andy Lamb put it down two minutes after me on just his second day of work. Sick!!

4 stars, one of my favorite alpine boulders ever. The only thing that detracts is the possibilty of an early easier exit to the arête, albeit over a terrifying landing. Regardless, I always dreamed about finding a 30 foot 45 degree wall with perfect edges and that pinch! Props again to Charlie and Creg for the find, Mark for the FA, and Clara for hiking up there tirelessly. Closing this chapter and opening a new one in Tuolumne boulder development, projects as far as the eye can see!!!		 ***34b5a7cd
fa19f29d14-04-23 fa19f29dUnder the Skin Indian Rock FAfa19f29d fa19f29dThe shoulder project at one of the oldest bouldering areas in the world (across the street from mortar)...starts on the Seam, right hand to rounded crosly edge, left to terrible pinch, hard high step to the hardest shoulder move I've ever done. Not sure of the grade, two pieced in 10 minutes my first day on it in perfect conditions, then took 5-6 more days. Feels harder than Chinese, easier than Impossible; several others think 8B.

Shoulder/bicep tendinitis thing seems to be in remission, fingers crossed... Been off the grid for a while, good to be back!!		 **fa19f29d

c3b851da12-09-09 c3b851daThe Bay View Crimp Problem Mt. Tam / the bay view boulder Soft, FAc3b851da c3b851daTook a while to log this thing, couldn't decide on a name, so just went back to basics...

Start on two-finger pocket crimp and side pull dish, reach up to tiny 3 finger crimp and lock off/lurp to left hand razor, then pogo to the sloper out right...the most straight forward hard problem i've ever done, "this is bouldering"

Went from not being able to pull on the wall, to doing it in an hour, last go/best go! V6 lock-off to a V9/10 deadpoint, to a V9/10 dyno = V12.0? falls right between the grades. Marky Mark got the 2nd and confirmed the slash grade haha.

A nice basalt wall 10 feet from the road with a gorgeous view of SF and the bay. The pinch problem will go next time out! Should be a popular one for the bay area gym rats!		 **c3b851da
